      "writtenOn": "2021-03-19T16:05:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Two suggestions:\n- We should remove the left band from the fiddle which contains an opaque color; it adds extra LOC to the fiddle code and gives the reader more to try to reason about in the output image. The gradient bands are enough to tell the tale (IMO).\n\n- We should add a brief description here, explaining the output image. The fiddle code does this very well, but \"read English\" is a much lower bar than \"read and understand a fiddle.\" e.g.\n\n\"The image below demonstrates the difference: properly premultiplied colors produce a smooth gradient as alpha decreases. Unpremultipled colors cause the gradient to display incorrectly, with a shift in hue as the alpha changes. This hue shift is caused by Skia clamping the color\u0027s RGB values to its alpha.\"",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 71,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 71,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "6c794362eb996718141bc6fd88b25f283afe001c",
